OL,3,CBomb neighbours should not have to
OL,4,C'foot the bill' for damage, say MPs
OL,6,F"I've lost all my pots. I lost the
OL,7,Ftrees, lost my plants, I lost a lot of
OL,8,Fstuff that was given to me, which
OL,9,Fwon't be replaced," he said.JMartyn
OL,10,Fsaid he had experienced fantastic
OL,11,Fsupport from Plymouth City Council,
OL,12,Fbut ultimately the question of "who
OL,13,Fwill pay?" is down to insurers.
OL,15,FThree years ago a bomb was detonated
OL,16,Fin Exeter, causing significant damage.
OL,18,F, but lost, as judges ruled it was an
OL,19,F"act of war" and not covered by
OL,20,Finsurance.
